Class GuiItemSlot<T extends AbstractItemStack>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.maxstupo.flatengine.hgui.AbstractNode

        • com.github.maxstupo.flatengine.hgui.GuiImage
          • com.github.maxstupo.flatengine.hgui.GuiItemSlot<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the item stack type it must derive from AbstractItemStack.

    public class GuiItemSlot<T extends AbstractItemStack>
extends GuiImage
    This GUI node represents a item slot, it can contain a stack of items defined by the interface AbstractItemStack.
    Author:
    Maxstupo

    • Constructor Detail

      • GuiItemSlot

        public GuiItemSlot(AbstractScreen screen,
                   float localX,
                   float localY,
                   int size,
                   T contents,
                   boolean isTakeOnly,
                   ISlotLogic logic,
                   T holding)
        Create a new GuiItemSlot object.
        Parameters:
        screen - the screen that owns this node.
        localX - the local x position.
        localY - the local y position.
        size - the size of this square item slot.
        contents - the contents stored within this item slot, can't be null.
        isTakeOnly - true if this item slot can remove items only.
        logic - the slot logic for this item slot.
        holding - the item stack that is held. This is used to share an item stack between multiple item slots.
